TEXAS EASTERN TRANSMISSION CORPORATION, ETC., PLAINTIFF-RESPONDENT, v. WILDLIFE PRESERVES, INC., ETC., DEFENDANT-APPELLANT. Superior Court of New Jersey Appellate Division Argued March 7, 1966 Decided March 14, 1966.

Before Judges Goldmann and Foley.

Mr. Francis E. P. McCarter argued the cause for appellant (Mr. Stuart A. Young, Jr., attorney; Mr. McCarter and Mr. Charles R. Merrill on the brief). Mr. Thomas J. Bitar argued the cause for respondent (Messrs. Jeffers & Mountain, attorneys; Mr. Robert J. Del Tufo, on the brief). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed, essentially for the reasons expressed in the opinion of Judge Long, reported in 89 N. J. Super. 1 (Law. Div. 1965).
